==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic *''fiskaz'', from Indo-European ''*peisk-, pisk-''.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian ''[[fisk]]'', Old Saxon ''[[#Old Saxon|fisc]]'' (Dutch ''[[visch]]''), Old High German ''[[#Old High German|fisc]]'' (German ''[[Fisch]]''), Old Norse ''[[fiskr]]'' (Swedish ''[[fisk]]''), Gothic [[𐍆𐌹𐍃𐌺𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin ''[[piscis]]'', Russian [[пискарь]], Irish ''[[iasc]]''.

